When I was in kindergarten there was this kid who would always mess with me but I didn't really care until one day I brought a book about cars that my mother had just bought for me as a birthday present because I loved cars to school. and when it was time for recess I brought it with me and looked at it for a little bit but then decided I wanted to go on the swings so I went to my teacher who was sitting at a picnic table near the playground and asked her to watch my book until recess was over. so she took my book and I went to go play on the swings but then I looked over and saw the same stupid kid who would always bully me pick up my book at the table which my teacher was no longer sitting at (she had gone inside for some reason). so I got up and started running towards the kid to get my book but before I could get to him he just started tearing apart my book for no reason I kept running at him saying stop that's mine then he turns around and simply says no it's not then throws what's left of my book on the ground and runs away. then I started crying while trying to pick up all the pieces of my book off the ground 3 minutes later my teacher came back outside and saw me crying and asked what was wrong so I told her what happened and she brought me inside and lazily tried to put my book back together with scotch tape. then I went home and had to tell my mother what happened and it made her cry when I showed her the book it felt horrible to see my mother cry and I felt like it was my fault because I didn't keep the book safe. then about 7 years later I was riding my bike down the road and I saw the kid who had torn my book apart walking down the street so I stopped my bike and just stared at him and had never felt such anger in my life my hands clinched the handle bars of my bike so hard my skin started to burn. luckily he had his head to the ground so I don't think he noticed me starring at him then after he had kept walking and was far out of sight I still just stood there in the same spot on the side of the road still so angry that I didn't want to move. then I started biting my nails out of stress and stood there biting my nails for about 20 minutes before I felt a stinging pain in my left index finger then looked down and noticed that I had bitten off a huge part of my nail and it was bleeding pretty bad. so I rode home on my bike and washed my bloody hand off and put a bandage on it then found the taped together book that I kept and just looked through it while I cried thinking about that moment again and how it felt when it made my mother cry. And still to this day that memory sometimes randomly pops up in my mind and I get so angry that I can't think or do anything it's like a curse that probably haunt me forever.
